<h4>What stipend (pay) should I offer a trainee?</h4>
<p>
The stipend you offer is up to you, however, we suggest that paid positions be enough to cover
living and expenses. Normally the trainee will get around $1000-1500/month. There are also
some positions without any stipend; however, this is typically only for short-term programs (6
months maximum) where the trainee can gain invaluable experience.</p>

<a href="#top" class="grey">back to top</a>


<h4>Can our trainee get a part time or a second job while on a J-1 visa?</h4>

<p>No. J-1 participants are not allowed to be trained at any employer other than the host company
listed on Form DS-2019.</p>


<a href="#top" class="grey">back to top</a>



<h4>Can our trainee change the host company during the program?</h4>

<p>No. The host company is specified on Form DS-2019. If terms or conditions change during the
course of the training, CSB must be notified to determine if they warrant a transfer of training
site.</p>

<a href="#top" class="grey">back to top</a>


<h4>What if we are not happy with our trainee?</h4>

<p>Should any issues arise between a host company and a trainee, we advise to contact CSB right
away. We will try to work with you and the trainee to find a solution. If a solution cannot be
found, you are permitted to terminate the participant as you would any trainee or employee,
with suitable documentation.</p>

<a href="#top" class="grey">back to top</a>


<h4>What if we have to terminate the program?</h4>

<p>If the host company decides to terminate the trainee, he/she will become invalid and the
participant must exit the U.S. Please contact CSB immediately should any such problems arise.</p>


